div.p:
Have resolved, with a view to accomplishing these purposes, to
                                conclude a treaty to limit their respective naval armament, and to
                                that end have appointed as their Plenipotentiaries;

list.item:
The Right Honourable Sir Auckland Campbell Geddes, K. C.
                                        B., His Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the
                                        United States of America;

for the Dominion of Canada:
The
                                        Right Honourable Sir Robert Laird Borden, G. C. M. G., K.
                                        C;

for India:
The Right Honourable
                                        Valingman Sankaranarayana Srinivasa Sastri, Member of the
                                        Indian Council of State;

Mr. Jules J. Jusserand, Ambassador Extraordinary and
                                        Plenipotentiary to the United States of America, Grand Cross
                                        of the National Order of the Legion of Honour;

The Honourable Vittorio Rolandi Ricci, Senator of the
                                        Kingdom, His Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary at
                                        Washington;

Baron Tomosaburo Kato, Minister for the Navy, Junii, a
                                        member of the First Class of the Imperial Order of the Grand
                                        Cordon of the Rising Sun with the Paulownia Flower;

Baron Kijuro Shidehara, His Ambassador Extraordinary and
                                        Plenipotentiary at Washington, Joshii, a member of the First
                                        Class of the Imperial Order of the Rising Sun;

Mr. Masanao Hanihara, Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs,
                                        Jushii, a member of the Second Class of the Imperial Order
                                        of the Rising Sun;
